<component id="ID_txtTitle_02">
<text><![CDATA[Broadcast]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtBody_02">
<text><![CDATA[The broadcast bit indicates to the receiving interface that the frame is destined for all or a group of end stations on the LAN segment.]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtTitle2_02">
<text><![CDATA[Local]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtBody2_02">
<text><![CDATA[The Local bit indicates if the 24-bit vendor number can be modified locally.]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtTitle3_02">
<text><![CDATA[OUI Number]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtBody3_02">
<text><![CDATA[The OUI number is 22 bits long. It is assigned by IEEE and it identifies the manufacturer of the NIC card.]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtTitle4_02">
<text><![CDATA[OUI]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtBody4_02">
<text><![CDATA[The OUI is 24 bits long and is made up the broadcast, local and OUI number fields.]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtTitle5_02">
<text><![CDATA[Vendor Number / Assignment]]></text>
</component>
<component id="ID_txtBody5_02">
<text><![CDATA[The vendor assignment part of the MAC address is a 24 bit long number (vendor number) that uniquely identifies the Ethernet hardware.]]></text>
</component>
